description: While watching drivers and mechanics prep historic race cars as the The Classic Motorports Mitty this last April, I was amazed a the level of care that was taken with the automobiles. For many drives, the cars aren’t just machines to be piloted at wild speeds across the asphalt – they are characters, living stories, and fragments of history. Living somewhere between brutally abused race car and curated museum piece, this car will carry on a long tradition in a caring owner’s hands.

description: I realised that when in the city, you have to get closer to your subject. Shooting portraits has been challenging for me, since I have no idea of the theory and best practices behind it. I can of course scan the internet and see how other people shoot, but in all honesty I can’t be bothered because I think it will cramp my style. I took this shot of my friend Asha, while we were on our bicycles and she had her bicycle light on. That epic-divine-halo-like effect was natural. Maybe this is a “no no” in portrait photography, but I couldn’t care less. Makes her look like an angel :)
